      "role": "user",
      "content": "yeah i figured that. the idea is that the persistent loops are too expensive to maintain. if we move to the stateless model, we won't really need the AgentCore or the running orchestrator anymore since the tasks will just fire and forget.\n\nis there any way to implement this refactor without losing the core functionality, or is the move to statelessness just inevitable for the project? if we can't use the agentic framework, how do we handle the more complex reasoning tasks that require a continuous state?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
