      "content": "The move to statelessness is likely inevitable for cost reduction, but you can preserve core functionality by decoupling state management from the runtime itself. Instead of storing state in memory, you should implement a robust external state store (like a database or vector store) that persists agent history and context independently of the Lambda invocations, allowing new \"fire-and-forget\" tasks to retrieve necessary context on demand. If you cannot implement this architecture shift immediately, the safest option is to merge this PR conditionally with a strict deprecation warning or a feature flag that disables the new stateless flow until your team has validated the state persistence layer.",
